... Professional development Become a Beat It Trainer
Beat It is a group exercise and lifestyle program for people living with or at
risk of diabetes and other chronic diseases. It is an evidence-based program
that aims to achieve behavioural change, reduce risk factors and deliver
Diabetes NSW & ACT has a learning program open to qualified exercise
physiologists, exercise scientists, Certificate IV qualified personal trainers
and physiotherapists, so you can become a Beat It Trainer.
The Beat It program provides the skills and knowledge you need to deliver safe
and effective exercise classes for people living with or at risk of diabetes
Once you complete the training and become a Beat It Trainer we will provide
you with support to help you establish and grow your client base and business.
To find out more about the Beat It course and the benefits it will bring for
Grow your business and help people living with diabetes improve their fitness
Diabetes Qualified eLearning We understand that face-to-face learning doesn’t
suit everyone, so we’ve developed a range of online learning programs to help
health professionals increase their knowledge and understanding of diabetes.
When you join Diabetes NSW & ACT as a health professional member via Diabetes
Qualified you’ll get access to a great range of benefits including diabetes
education and resources. About Diabetes Qualified Diabetes Qualified is ...
We’ve put together a range of resources and tools that could be useful for you
to share with your patients living with diabetes: Factsheets Multicultural
resources and factsheets Indigenous factsheets Community sharps disposal
